text:
RT @charlie_savage: The House will vote on banning 215 orders to get Americans' Internet browsing data. Compromise is ambiguous, sets up a FISA court fight over whether it applies when FBI doesn't know ahead of time if US data will be swept in, e.g. visitors to ISIS websites.
